This paper is about reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on a distributional approach to reinforcement learning, which involves modeling the distribution over returns instead of just estimating the mean. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most general category for machine learning research. 

Additionally, the paper involves theoretical and algorithmic results, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

The paper also evaluates the proposed algorithm on Atari 2600 games, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). 

Overall, the most likely categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE, and cs.SY, in that order.
